dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Economic Development. Division of Planning and Development. Atlas Sheet 28 (1949) New Jersey Geological Survey. Alternate title: [New Jersey.] Atlas sheet no. 29. Relief shown by 10 feet contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by soundings in feet at low tide. Title was not given. Region covered: Trenton and eastward. Original survey made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer 1880-3. 1949 revision by R. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1949.
